### Verifying Selector Re-renders with createSelectorTestCase Spy (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/recharts/recharts/blob/main/test/README.md

Illustrates how to utilize the `spy` object returned by `createSelectorTestCase` to track and assert the number of times a selector is invoked. This technique is essential for identifying and preventing unnecessary re-renders in Recharts components, thus improving performance. The example shows how initial renders and prop changes affect the selector's call count.

```ts
  const { spy, rerenderSameComponent } = renderTestCase(mySelector);
  expect(spy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1); // Initial render
  rerenderSameComponent();
  expect(spy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1); // No re-render
  rerenderSameComponent({ someProp: newValue });
  expect(spy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2); // Re-rendered due to prop change
```

